The Ministry of Communications and Information Technology (Burmese: ဆက်သွယ်ရေးနှင့် သတင်းအချက်အလက် နည်းပညာဝန်ကြီးဌာန; abbreviated MCIT) administers Myanmar's communications and information technology policies. The ministry was formerly known as the Ministry of Communications, Posts and Telegraphs.
The Ministry was organized as Ministry of Transport and Communication by Htin Kyaw's Cabinet in 2016.
